name: Neighbourhood Series - Toa Payoh Playground
description: The Kim Keat Toa Payoh dinosaur playground was built in 2000, while it is not an old landmark playground in Singapore, it was unique and iconic, using dinosaurs as its theme. The playground's centrepiece is a huge brown tyrannosaurus, about 3m tall. I find it quite amusing to see big statues of dinosaurs in a quiet, older public housing estate.
